  "title": "Layers",
  "description": "Mineral permits and applications with boundaries and permit status.",
  "abstract": "This is a map image layer provided by New Zealand Petroleum &amp; Minerals (NZP&amp;M) to show current mineral permits and applications in New Zealand. This map image layer is used in the Minerals Permit Webmaps GIS app.Minerals Permit Webmaps -  https://gis.nzpam.govt.nz/permitwebmaps/?commodity=mineralsNZP&amp;M provides online maps using real-time data to show all current petroleum permits and applications in New Zealand. The maps are updated through our permit register system and GIS database. You can print out maps, or download the data as shapefiles. A user guide is available here. Layers included in this map image layer:Minerals Permit Applications - Spatial representation of areas under application for prospecting, exploration, or mining permits for mineralsMineral Active Permits - Spatial representation of active permits for minerals prospecting, exploration or mining. This layer includes permits granted under the Crown Minerals Act 1991, licences granted under previous legislation, and areas designated as Gold Fossicking AreasMinerals Extension of Land - Spatial representation of areas where permit holders have applied to extend the area covered by an existing minerals prospecting, exploration, or mining permitPending Contest Round - Spatial representation of areas to be released as Newly Available Acreage or Competitive TenderOpen Contest Round - Spatial representation of areas currently open for competitive applications as Newly Available Acreage or Competitive TenderClosed Contest Round - Spatial representation of closed Newly Available Acreage, Competitive Tender, and Equal Priority in Time contest rounds where applications may be under evaluationReserved Area - Spatial representation of areas reserved from permitting under Section 28A of the Crown Minerals ActThese data are managed by the NZP&amp;M Geospatial team. If you have any questions about the data, please contact us at ERMGeospatial@mbie.govt.nz.",
